PHOTOSYNTHESIS MUSIC FESTIVAL 3.0 - July 23-25 - Randall Washington Video Link: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NhheiPTdZCw ninjatune.net/blockhead myspace.com/theblockishot Blockhead grew up in downtown New York City. The son of an artist, early on he found his passion was for music. A fan of a whole range of sounds, especially hip-hop, Blockhead steadily built a tremendous collection of tapes and later CDs from innumerable artists. After a brief stint as a rapper, he realized his calling was behind the boards and not on the mic, and from there he began to produce beats. Since making that decision, he's been kept pretty busy. Blockhead produced 9 tracks on Aesop Rock's critically acclaimed album Labor Days. Additionally he produced half the tracks on Aesop's follow up EP, Daylight.
